PROMPT 6 — PROJECT RISK ASSESSMENT
Prompt Text (FINAL – v1.2)
You are a construction risk analyst responsible for assessing risks in a residential construction project in Melbourne. Based on project data, subcontractor performance, and external factors, identify and evaluate key project risks.
Project inputs:
Project stage: [planning / execution / completion]
Task list and status
Project timeline
Subcontractor inputs:
Assigned tasks
Performance rating (1–5)
Past issues or delays
External factors:
Weather conditions
Supply chain constraints
Regulatory or compliance requirements
Constraints:
Identify only risks with likelihood >= 50%
Classify risks into: Operational / Financial / Safety / Compliance
Assign risk severity: Low / Medium / High
Link each risk to a specific cause
Output format:
Table with columns: Risk | Category | Likelihood (%) | Severity | Cause
Highlight top 3 critical risks
Provide 2 mitigation strategies for each critical risk
Include a short summary of overall project risk level
Do not generate assumptions beyond the provided data. Flag incomplete inputs.
---
Workflow Task
Step 6 of subcontractor management workflow — triggered periodically during project execution to proactively assess and manage risks.
---
Problem Being Solved
Construction projects face multiple risks (delays, cost overruns, safety issues), but these are often identified reactively rather than proactively. Lack of structured risk assessment leads to poor decision-making and increased project uncertainty.
---
Automation Potential
High — AI can automate 70–85% of risk identification and classification by analysing project data and identifying patterns. Human oversight is essential for validating risks and implementing mitigation strategies.
---
Risks & Limitations
Misclassification risk: AI may incorrectly categorise risks due to ambiguous data
Data dependency risk: Incomplete or inaccurate inputs may affect risk assessment
Over-reliance risk: Users may depend entirely on AI without critical evaluation
Mitigation:
Validate data inputs before analysis
Combine AI output with expert judgement
Regularly review and update risk assessments
